    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4574: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                            type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-04T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 4, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 4—2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. In first stage afternoon meeting of the General Commission of the
                        Assembly<note n="45" xml:id="d544fn45">See League of Nations, <hi
                            rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, Special Supplement No. 101, vol.
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 38–43.</note> conflict was precipitated
                    on the question of fact concerning the cessation of hostilities and proposal
                    made that the qualified military authorities of the principal interested powers
                    should be instructed to report immediately as to the facts. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PBJ1"
                        >Boncour</persName> and the Italian representative agreed so to do. If you
                    approve please send instructions to Shanghai immediately and notify me. Also
                    furnish me, as urgently as possible, any reply received for transmission to the
                    Secretary General.</p>
                <p>Should the military authorities decide to cooperate in one report I suggest
                    appropriate instructions be sent to our representative. Naturally I have made no
                    commitment on this subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
